addLiquidity(address,uint256).details: Allows users to add liquidity to the contract for a specific token

params.amount: The amount of tokens to add as liquidity
params.token: The address of the token for which liquidity is being added

addSupportedToken(address).details: Adds a token to the list of supported tokens

params.token: The address of the token to be added

constructor.details: Constructor that sets the owner of the contract

params.initialOwner: The address that will be set as the owner of the contract

getTokenBalance(address).details: Returns the balance of a specific token in the contract

params.token: The address of the token to check

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

pause().details: Allows the owner to pause the contract

paused().details: Returns true if the contract is paused, and false otherwise.

removeAllLiquidity(address).details: Allows the owner to remove all liquidity of a specific token

params.token: The address of the token to remove all liquidity

removeLiquidity(address,uint256).details: Allows the owner to remove liquidity from the contract

params.amount: The amount of tokens to remove
params.token: The address of the token to remove

removeSupportedToken(address).details: Removes a token from the list of supported tokens

params.token: The address of the token to be removed

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

setFee(uint256).details: Allows the owner to set a new fee rate

params.newFeeNumerator: The new fee numerator (actual fee = newFeeNumerator / FEE_DENOMINATOR)

swap(address,address,uint256,uint256).details: Performs a token swap between two supported tokens

params.amountIn: The amount of fromToken to swap
params.fromToken: The address of the token to swap from
params.minAmountOut: The minimum amount of toToken expected to receive
params.toToken: The address of the token to swap to

syncBalance(address).details: Synchronizes the contract's internal balance with the actual token balance

params.token: The address of the token to synchronize

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

unpause().details: Allows the owner to unpause the contract

withdrawToken(address,uint256).details: Allows the owner to withdraw tokens from the contract

params.amount: The amount of tokens to withdraw
params.token: The address of the token to withdraw
